featured_reviews.review_id:
Assalamualaikum.
This is very good Shaafi mathab masjid.
Big space with air conditioner.
Every ramalan Sahar meels are provided on this masjid.
To get Sahar meel we have to inform to the incharge person before starting ramalan month.

Actually this  'the Great' mosques. It makes a rather modest impression with two Egyptian style minarets and a hall of some 10m in height in brownish colors. Perhaps this is the reason I liked this mosque.
Inside the lowered lamps create a more intimate atmosphere. The believers make a relaxed, but sincere impression. Most come to pray, others to be taught. Some to take a nap. The interior lacks a lot of decoration and has been kept simple.
Also worth visiting in the evening when the minarets are brightly illuminated and there are spot lights on the mosque's walls.
